Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{to taste}ed water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Peel and finely chop @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} and pat dry with #paper towels{}. Pat @scallops{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Place shrimp and scallops in a #medium bowl{}; toss with lemon zest, ¼ of the garlic, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp} (add more for an extra kick, or leave it out if you're feeling spice-averse!). Season with salt and pepper.

> Add more chili flakes for extra heat, or skip if you prefer milder dishes.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Heat a large pan over high heat. Once pan is hot, add shrimp and scallop mixture; spread out in an even layer and cook, stirring once, until opaque and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted and coated.

Turn off heat; transfer to a second medium bowl (along with any cooking liquid).

Once spaghetti is done, melt @butter{2%tbsp} in pan used for shrimp and scallops over medium heat. Add remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2} and ¼ cup pasta cooking water. Simmer until sauce has slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir drained spaghetti, shrimp and scallops (and any cooking liquid), @garlic herb butter{2%tbsp}, half the parsley, and half the @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} into pan with sauce. Toss to coat. Add splashes of reserved pasta cooking water as necessary, until everything is thoroughly coated in sauce.

> TIP: If cheese clumps, continue stirring and adding more pasta cooking water until smooth!

Remove from heat and stir in a big squeeze of lemon juice. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Top with remaining parsley, remaining Parmesan, and chili flakes to taste. Add a big squeeze of lemon juice over top and serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.